name: Jena Griswold
tweet: In terms of the voting eligible population, our turnout rate was 76.4%, which is the second highest turnout in the nation! Congrats, Minnesota for taking first place. We look forward to taking that spot in 2022!

name: Jena Griswold
tweet: Colorado’s turnout rate was over 86% of active voters for this election!

name: Jena Griswold
tweet: “Election officials will stand up and follow the rules, follow the laws to make sure their voters have their voices heard and…democracy will prevail.” Thank you @KateBolduan for having me on!   https://t.co/7OdYEauX8O

name: Jena Griswold
tweet: Many women elected leaders are on the front lines of protecting our democracy. The work isn’t always easy, especially with misinformation and threats. I stand with @secretaryhobbs, @JocelynBenson, @KathyBoockvar, and all the incredible people dedicated to free & fair elections.

name: Jena Griswold
tweet: This is leadership and commitment. Thank you @C_C_Krebs for being such a fantastic partner to states in securing elections. #Protect2020 #TrustedInfo2020

name: Jena Griswold
tweet: Teams of republican and democratic election workers & poll watchers from both parties oversee the election process. They are key to America’s elections.

name: Jena Griswold
tweet: Election night results are never final results in any statewide election. Some states weren’t able to start counting ballots until Monday or Tuesday, and that’s okay. All the votes must be counted before the results are final.

name: Jena Griswold
tweet: We stop the count when all military and overseas ballots & cured ballots are counted on November 13. Thank you to all Americans serving our nation.

name: Jena Griswold
tweet: I am proud of Colorado’s elections and the voting access that we have added over the last two years. I also commend the county election officials, election judges, and the employees of the Department of State for doing such a tremendous job!

name: Jena Griswold
tweet: More Coloradans voted in this election than in any previous election in our state’s history! Over 3.3 million Coloradans voted, with an 86.8% turnout among active registered voters. And even more ballots will be processed in the coming days!

name: Jena Griswold
tweet: Colorado, what a great election! We had a record number of Coloradans vote, and are still processing ballots. Every ballot will be counted.

name: Jena Griswold
tweet: Presidential Election - Colorado Preliminary Election Results with approx. 2.19M ballots reported  Trump (R): 41.49% (903,003) Biden (D): 56.19% (1,222,863)  Follow the #Election2020 results:  https://t.co/zwo0Ut4Db6

name: Jena Griswold
tweet: US Senate - Colorado Preliminary Election Results with approx. 2.1M ballots reported  Hickenlooper (D) 54.81% (1,151,027) Gardner (R) 43.17% (906,430)  Follow the results:  https://t.co/zwo0Ut4Db6

name: Jena Griswold
tweet: After 7 PM tonight when Colorado polls close, you can find preliminary election results at  https://t.co/zwo0Ut4Db6. I’ll also be sharing some of the preliminary results here. #Election2020  Reminder: As long as you’re in line by 7pm, you can register and vote!

name: Jena Griswold
tweet: Since the last update, more than 100,000 additional votes have been cast. Vote totals are at 3,104,807 as of 4pm.

name: Jena Griswold
tweet: Today is your last chance to have your vote counted!  ⏳ Ballots must be received by county clerks by no later than 7:00 PM, so drop off your ballot ASAP! #VOTE  Any last-minute questions? 👉  https://t.co/sIAvUsoCON

name: Jena Griswold
tweet: UPDATE: As of noon today, over 3 million Coloradans have voted, which is a 79.5% turnout rate among active registered voters. Keep it up, Colorado!

name: Jena Griswold
tweet: Election Day is here! If you haven't voted:  📩 Drop off your ballot ASAP at a ballot dropbox near you 🗳 You can also register and/or vote in-person at a voting center ✅ Head to  https://t.co/sIAvUsoCON to find a nearby voting location  #VOTE | #VOTE | #VOTE

name: Jena Griswold
tweet: BREAKING: Colorado has surpassed 2016 turnout with 2,893,395 people having voted as of 10am. You have until 7pm tonight to vote! Visit  https://t.co/7LWUA0u9UL for more information!

name: Jena Griswold
tweet: Over 2.8 Million Coloradans have voted already! We are 20,748 votes short of exceeding the total 2016 turnout. Voting centers open in 5 minutes - make sure to cast your ballot today!

name: Jena Griswold
tweet: Coloradans, have you made your plan to vote? Tomorrow is the last day to cast your ballot!  Join the 2,765,244 voters in our great state who have submitted their ballots. You can easily drop off your mail ballot or vote in-person. Whatever is best for you, #MakeAPlan today!

name: Jena Griswold
tweet: Vote!

name: Jena Griswold
tweet: Voting numbers from last night are compiled: 2,533,050 Coloradans have voted! Here’s the breakdown by voter registration-      ✅ 852,848 registered democrats      ✅ 715,988 registered republicans      ✅ 930,962 unaffiliated voters  This is 88.7% of the 2016 turnout!

name: Jena Griswold
tweet: High turnout in Colorado continues, with over 2.4 million voters submitting their ballots so far! That’s over 85% of our total 2016 turnout.  #Vote if you haven’t yet, by dropping off your ballot or voting in-person at a nearby voting center. Questions?  https://t.co/sIAvUsoCON!
